WEBVTT
X-TIMESTAMP-MAP=MPEGTS:900000,LOCAL:00:00:00.000

00:00:15.598 --> 00:00:16.599 position:50% align:center
[KYO groaning]

00:00:16.683 --> 00:00:17.851 position:50% align:center
[UOTANI]
How much did you grow over...?

00:00:17.934 --> 00:00:21.396 position:50% align:center
Sorry. She, well,
she gets worked up.

00:00:21.479 --> 00:00:23.648 position:50% align:center
[UOTANI] You people shoot
up overnight like weeds.

00:00:23.732 --> 00:00:25.483 position:50% align:center
You're not exactly
short, Arisa.

00:00:25.567 --> 00:00:27.986 position:50% align:center
I won't be satisfied
until I'm 5'11"!

00:00:28.069 --> 00:00:31.156 position:50% align:center
Ah, yes, the familiar sounds
of a new term starting.

00:00:31.239 --> 00:00:33.074 position:50% align:center
Welcome back, everyone.

00:00:33.158 --> 00:00:34.826 position:50% align:center
The break obviously
didn't do much for you

00:00:34.909 --> 00:00:36.995 position:50% align:center
in the femininity department.

00:00:37.078 --> 00:00:38.329 position:50% align:center
Maybe you should just give up.

00:00:38.413 --> 00:00:40.081 position:50% align:center
Heh. Yeah, maybe I will.

00:00:40.165 --> 00:00:42.250 position:50% align:center
What's the point
in trying, anyway?

00:00:42.334 --> 00:00:45.211 position:50% align:center
Can't even get one man
to give me a second look.

00:00:45.295 --> 00:00:46.504 position:50% align:center
Is she okay?

00:00:46.588 --> 00:00:49.299 position:50% align:center
Okay? No, not even close.

00:00:49.382 --> 00:00:51.301 position:50% align:center
Her special friend from
the convenience store

00:00:51.384 --> 00:00:54.095 position:50% align:center
has failed to make
another appearance.

00:00:54.179 --> 00:00:57.015 position:50% align:center
You can see it, plain as day.

00:00:57.098 --> 00:01:00.018 position:50% align:center
The aura of a woman
desperately in love.

00:01:00.101 --> 00:01:01.436 position:50% align:center
[TOHRU]
Yeah.

00:01:01.519 --> 00:01:04.856 position:50% align:center
Now that you mention it,
she does seem pretty upset.

00:01:04.939 --> 00:01:06.983 position:50% align:center
Indeed. It's hard to watch.

00:01:07.067 --> 00:01:08.610 position:50% align:center
[KYO]
That's funny.

00:01:08.693 --> 00:01:11.321 position:50% align:center
Never thought I'd see you
getting flustered over someone.

00:01:11.404 --> 00:01:13.156 position:50% align:center
Huh. Interesting.

00:01:13.239 --> 00:01:15.325 position:50% align:center
That you would say
something like that.

00:01:15.408 --> 00:01:17.660 position:50% align:center
Uh. What's that mean?

00:01:19.579 --> 00:01:22.582 position:50% align:center
Wait, hold on! You didn't
read my mind, did you?

00:01:22.665 --> 00:01:25.043 position:50% align:center
My waves don't give me the
ability to read minds.

00:01:25.126 --> 00:01:27.420 position:50% align:center
I just remembered
something amusing.

00:01:27.504 --> 00:01:29.339 position:50% align:center
Probably best if we
leave it at that.

00:01:29.422 --> 00:01:31.174 position:50% align:center
[KYO]
Did you or not?!

00:03:04.517 --> 00:03:06.394 position:50% align:center
[MOTOKO]
Yuki!

00:03:06.478 --> 00:03:08.146 position:50% align:center
These are for you.

00:03:08.229 --> 00:03:10.732 position:50% align:center
A souvenir of Summer
Sweetheart biscuits.

00:03:10.815 --> 00:03:12.734 position:50% align:center
I hope you like them.

00:03:12.817 --> 00:03:15.111 position:50% align:center
Oh. Thanks, that's really nice.

00:03:15.195 --> 00:03:18.114 position:50% align:center
I feel bad, though.
I didn't get you anything.

00:03:18.198 --> 00:03:21.242 position:50% align:center
It's fine. Just giving you
a gift is enough for me.

00:03:21.326 --> 00:03:22.660 position:50% align:center
She's right!

00:03:22.744 --> 00:03:24.329 position:50% align:center
You don't need to worry about
that kinda stuff, Yuki.

00:03:24.412 --> 00:03:26.373 position:50% align:center
[MOTOKO] Simply grace me
with a grateful smile,

00:03:26.456 --> 00:03:29.084 position:50% align:center
and it will be the only gift
I could ever need.

00:03:29.167 --> 00:03:31.086 position:50% align:center
Upon it, I will soar,

00:03:31.169 --> 00:03:34.089 position:50% align:center
rising high into the heavens
on pure white wings.

00:03:34.172 --> 00:03:36.257 position:50% align:center
[KINOSHITA]
Flying through the endless sky,

00:03:36.341 --> 00:03:38.885 position:50% align:center
hearts expanding to hold
a love so deep and true

00:03:38.968 --> 00:03:40.512 position:50% align:center
it almost hurts.

00:03:40.595 --> 00:03:41.888 position:50% align:center
[KINOSHITA, MOKOTO sighing]

00:03:41.971 --> 00:03:42.889 position:50% align:center
[YUKI]
Minagawa- <i>senpai</i> ?

00:03:42.972 --> 00:03:45.558 position:50% align:center
Ah! I'm sorry. I got distracted.

00:03:45.642 --> 00:03:47.477 position:50% align:center
The beginnings of a poem
just popped into my head

00:03:47.560 --> 00:03:48.436 position:50% align:center
out of nowhere!

00:03:48.520 --> 00:03:50.188 position:50% align:center
What a coincidence. Me, too.

00:03:50.271 --> 00:03:51.898 position:50% align:center
Who cares about dumb poetry?

00:03:51.981 --> 00:03:54.818 position:50% align:center
Now, Senpai, tell us what
you did over summer break!

00:03:54.901 --> 00:03:57.278 position:50% align:center
[BOTH]
What do you mean, "dumb poetry"?

00:03:57.362 --> 00:03:59.489 position:50% align:center
Went to the beach. That's all.

00:03:59.572 --> 00:04:02.325 position:50% align:center
[YAMAGISHI] Ooh, a beach
vacation! Sounds like fun.

00:04:02.409 --> 00:04:06.079 position:50% align:center
[KIMI] Wow! You're a super
popular guy, huh?

00:04:06.162 --> 00:04:08.081 position:50% align:center
Good for you!

00:04:08.164 --> 00:04:10.125 position:50% align:center
[giggles]

00:04:10.208 --> 00:04:11.501 position:50% align:center
[gasps]

00:04:11.584 --> 00:04:14.671 position:50% align:center
Well, hello. What do ya got
there? Something yummy?

00:04:14.754 --> 00:04:16.006 position:50% align:center
Um.

00:04:16.089 --> 00:04:17.048 position:50% align:center
[YAMAGISHI, MOTOKO, KINOSHITA]
Who is that girl?

00:04:17.132 --> 00:04:18.299 position:50% align:center
[KINOSHITA gasps]

00:04:18.383 --> 00:04:20.552 position:50% align:center
Minami! If you know who
she is, speak up now.

00:04:20.635 --> 00:04:22.220 position:50% align:center
[KINOSHITA]
She's in class 2-A.

00:04:22.303 --> 00:04:25.682 position:50% align:center
They say she's a temptress
who seduces men with her looks.

00:04:25.765 --> 00:04:26.891 position:50% align:center
...Yun-Yun.

00:04:26.975 --> 00:04:29.144 position:50% align:center
[ALL]
"Yun-Yun"?!

00:04:29.227 --> 00:04:30.520 position:50% align:center
Sorry?

00:04:30.603 --> 00:04:32.605 position:50% align:center
[MOTOKO] That's it!
Just who do you think you are?

00:04:32.689 --> 00:04:34.315 position:50% align:center
Showing up out of
nowhere like this!

00:04:34.399 --> 00:04:37.277 position:50% align:center
And then daring to refer to
him as Yu-- No! I can't!

00:04:37.360 --> 00:04:39.612 position:50% align:center
You don't get to pick out
some weird nickname for him!

00:04:39.696 --> 00:04:42.741 position:50% align:center
What's with that? Are you,
like, mocking us or something?

00:04:42.824 --> 00:04:45.869 position:50% align:center
[KIMI]
Ooo. You're pretty scary.

00:04:45.952 --> 00:04:47.912 position:50% align:center
And, yeah, sure am!

00:04:48.955 --> 00:04:51.499 position:50% align:center
[YUKI] Can we talk for a second?
It won't take long.

00:04:51.583 --> 00:04:53.585 position:50% align:center
Sure. Let's go!

00:04:54.627 --> 00:04:55.962 position:50% align:center
[KIMI laughs]

00:04:56.046 --> 00:04:57.380 position:50% align:center
[KIMI]
That was so funny!

00:04:57.464 --> 00:05:00.508 position:50% align:center
Ha! Did you see the
looks on their faces?

00:05:00.592 --> 00:05:01.634 position:50% align:center
[YUKI]
Would you laugh as hard

00:05:01.718 --> 00:05:03.219 position:50% align:center
if you were the one
being made fun of?

00:05:03.303 --> 00:05:04.596 position:50% align:center
[gasps]

00:05:04.679 --> 00:05:06.139 position:50% align:center
[YUKI]
Who are you?

00:05:06.222 --> 00:05:08.475 position:50% align:center
And where'd you come up
with that nickname?

00:05:08.558 --> 00:05:10.393 position:50% align:center
Oh? What, Yun-yun?

00:05:10.477 --> 00:05:13.605 position:50% align:center
I mean, Kimi wasn't the one
who first started using it.

00:05:13.688 --> 00:05:16.066 position:50% align:center
[YUKI] Uh. Someone else
calls me that? Who?

00:05:16.149 --> 00:05:18.234 position:50% align:center
Oh, Yun-Yun, there you are!

00:05:18.318 --> 00:05:20.111 position:50% align:center
[YUKI]
Why am I not surprised?

00:05:20.195 --> 00:05:21.863 position:50% align:center
[MANABE]
Long time no see, Yun-Yun!

00:05:21.946 --> 00:05:24.783 position:50% align:center
How was your summer break, man?
All you could hope for?

00:05:24.866 --> 00:05:26.826 position:50% align:center
Mine was awesome--
totally jam packed.

00:05:26.910 --> 00:05:28.161 position:50% align:center
Dates practically every night.

00:05:28.244 --> 00:05:29.454 position:50% align:center
[YUKI]
What's with the nickname?

00:05:29.537 --> 00:05:31.790 position:50% align:center
If I had my way, it would
last all year long.

00:05:31.873 --> 00:05:34.042 position:50% align:center
But, no, school just
had to start again.

00:05:34.125 --> 00:05:35.460 position:50% align:center
Lame to the max, huh?

00:05:35.543 --> 00:05:37.879 position:50% align:center
Will you stop babbling
and answer the question?

00:05:37.962 --> 00:05:40.507 position:50% align:center
Uh-oh. Someone put on his
grumpy pants this morning.

00:05:40.590 --> 00:05:43.760 position:50% align:center
He isn't a big fan of the
nickname you gave him, Kakeru.

00:05:43.843 --> 00:05:46.638 position:50% align:center
But it's so cute. Like a name
you would give a panda.

00:05:46.721 --> 00:05:49.974 position:50% align:center
Usually people's nicknames are
shorter than their actual names.

00:05:50.058 --> 00:05:53.436 position:50% align:center
Oh, my bad. I guess I'm not
an expert on these things.

00:05:53.520 --> 00:05:55.021 position:50% align:center
But forget that!

00:05:55.105 --> 00:05:57.440 position:50% align:center
I was looking all over the
place for you, Yun-Yun.

00:05:57.524 --> 00:05:58.692 position:50% align:center
[KIMI]
Yeah, same here!

00:05:58.775 --> 00:06:01.528 position:50% align:center
That's why Kimi interrupted
before, Yun-Yun.

00:06:01.611 --> 00:06:05.031 position:50% align:center
[YUKI] Oh, no. I'm stuck
with it now, aren't I?

00:06:05.115 --> 00:06:08.827 position:50% align:center
Hey! Our fearless
leader has arrived!

00:06:11.329 --> 00:06:12.580 position:50% align:center
[gasps]

00:06:16.626 --> 00:06:20.005 position:50% align:center
I'm from class 1-C.
Naohito Sakuragi.

00:06:20.088 --> 00:06:22.674 position:50% align:center
I'm serving as one
of the secretaries.

00:06:22.757 --> 00:06:23.591 position:50% align:center
[YUKI]
Great.

00:06:23.675 --> 00:06:25.552 position:50% align:center
Truth is, it's a
tedious position

00:06:25.635 --> 00:06:27.971 position:50% align:center
and one I had no
interest in accepting,

00:06:28.054 --> 00:06:31.224 position:50% align:center
but that changed after I found
out you were president.

00:06:31.307 --> 00:06:32.851 position:50% align:center
I want you to remember this:

00:06:32.934 --> 00:06:34.269 position:50% align:center
First and foremost,
you are my riv--

00:06:34.352 --> 00:06:37.856 position:50% align:center
Your first love? How sweet!
Get 'im, short stack.

00:06:37.939 --> 00:06:39.899 position:50% align:center
I'll be here for moral
support if you need me.

00:06:39.983 --> 00:06:41.401 position:50% align:center
[NAOHITO]
I am of average height!

00:06:41.484 --> 00:06:45.739 position:50% align:center
Play nicely, you two. Oh,
I forgot to introduce myself.

00:06:45.822 --> 00:06:49.034 position:50% align:center
My name's Kimi Todo,
and I'm a secretary like him.

00:06:49.117 --> 00:06:51.327 position:50% align:center
What? You're on the
student council?

00:06:51.411 --> 00:06:53.580 position:50% align:center
I might get a little
confused sometimes,

00:06:53.663 --> 00:06:55.582 position:50% align:center
but you'll be patient
with me, right?

00:06:55.665 --> 00:06:57.917 position:50% align:center
Just wait. I'll give
it my all, Yun-Yun.

00:06:58.001 --> 00:06:59.502 position:50% align:center
I won't ever let you down.

00:06:59.586 --> 00:07:01.046 position:50% align:center
O... kay...

00:07:01.129 --> 00:07:04.632 position:50% align:center
Yeah, I don't blame you for
bein' worried, but never fear.

00:07:04.716 --> 00:07:07.093 position:50% align:center
The cutesy act's convincing,
but this girl's actually-- Ow.

00:07:07.177 --> 00:07:09.137 position:50% align:center
Shut up and mind
your own business.

00:07:09.220 --> 00:07:11.222 position:50% align:center
[MANABE]
Ow. That freakin' hurt!

00:07:11.306 --> 00:07:12.932 position:50% align:center
I got him back for you,
short stack.

00:07:13.016 --> 00:07:15.727 position:50% align:center
[NAOHITO]
Stop calling me that!

00:07:15.810 --> 00:07:18.813 position:50% align:center
[YUKI] Deep or shallow?
Friendly or hostile?

00:07:18.897 --> 00:07:21.274 position:50% align:center
They've got too many
personalities to keep track of.

00:07:21.358 --> 00:07:23.526 position:50% align:center
I don't understand these people.

00:07:23.610 --> 00:07:25.612 position:50% align:center
And if I don't understand them,

00:07:25.695 --> 00:07:29.324 position:50% align:center
then how in the world am
I supposed to lead them?

00:07:29.407 --> 00:07:30.867 position:50% align:center
[MANABE]
Hey, Prez.

00:07:30.950 --> 00:07:34.204 position:50% align:center
Wanna give us an
inspiring word or two?

00:07:34.287 --> 00:07:35.872 position:50% align:center
[YUKI]
That's right.

00:07:35.955 --> 00:07:40.210 position:50% align:center
I made a promise.
Time to keep it.

00:07:40.293 --> 00:07:42.879 position:50% align:center
[YUKI]
Hello, everyone. Welcome.

00:07:42.962 --> 00:07:44.881 position:50% align:center
I'm glad you're here.

00:07:44.964 --> 00:07:47.133 position:50% align:center
As members of the
student council,

00:07:47.217 --> 00:07:49.427 position:50% align:center
we have many important duties,

00:07:49.511 --> 00:07:53.223 position:50% align:center
and we'll have to work
together to fulfill them all.

00:07:53.306 --> 00:07:55.850 position:50% align:center
[YUKI] I promised myself,
no matter what,

00:07:55.934 --> 00:07:58.687 position:50% align:center
I wouldn't run anymore.

00:07:58.770 --> 00:08:02.190 position:50% align:center
[YUKI] I'm not perfect,
and I won't pretend to be.

00:08:02.273 --> 00:08:06.277 position:50% align:center
The truth is, I still
have a lot to learn.

00:08:06.361 --> 00:08:10.115 position:50% align:center
But I swear, I'll work hard.

00:08:10.198 --> 00:08:15.078 position:50% align:center
And I'm hoping... I can count
on all of you to work with me.

00:08:16.955 --> 00:08:19.290 position:50% align:center
[MANABE]
Sure thing!

00:08:19.374 --> 00:08:20.959 position:50% align:center
[chuckles]

00:08:21.042 --> 00:08:23.420 position:50% align:center
[MANABE]
All right!

00:08:23.503 --> 00:08:25.755 position:50% align:center
You heard the man, guys.
We're all in this together.

00:08:25.839 --> 00:08:26.339 position:50% align:center
Go team!

00:08:26.423 --> 00:08:27.674 position:50% align:center
We're together?

00:08:27.757 --> 00:08:29.134 position:50% align:center
So, you're actually gonna
pull your weight, then?

00:08:29.217 --> 00:08:30.927 position:50% align:center
Come on, what're you
talking about?

00:08:31.011 --> 00:08:32.971 position:50% align:center
I'm the vice president
of this outfit.

00:08:33.054 --> 00:08:35.682 position:50% align:center
I'm gonna work my
butt off, you'll see.

00:08:35.765 --> 00:08:36.641 position:50% align:center
[snores]

00:08:36.725 --> 00:08:39.102 position:50% align:center
[NAOHITO]
That is not working!

00:08:39.185 --> 00:08:41.312 position:50% align:center
Here we go.

00:08:41.396 --> 00:08:45.567 position:50% align:center
[bell tolls]

00:08:45.650 --> 00:08:48.945 position:50% align:center
[YUKI] To put it nicely, this
year's student council members

00:08:49.029 --> 00:08:51.865 position:50% align:center
have... challenging
personalities.

00:08:51.948 --> 00:08:53.658 position:50% align:center
[MOTOKO]
Todo, you should know,

00:08:53.742 --> 00:08:55.243 position:50% align:center
if you're causing
trouble for Yuki,

00:08:55.326 --> 00:08:57.245 position:50% align:center
there will be consequences.

00:08:57.328 --> 00:09:00.790 position:50% align:center
Cheekiness and rude remarks
are unacceptable.

00:09:00.874 --> 00:09:03.793 position:50% align:center
Aw. You guys don't need
to worry about me.

00:09:03.877 --> 00:09:07.088 position:50% align:center
I will be a good little
girl like I always am.

00:09:07.172 --> 00:09:09.299 position:50% align:center
Oh, Kimi almost forgot!

00:09:09.382 --> 00:09:11.217 position:50% align:center
Thank you so much for
those yummy biscuits

00:09:11.301 --> 00:09:12.927 position:50% align:center
you gave Yun-Yun the other day.

00:09:13.011 --> 00:09:16.598 position:50% align:center
He and I ate them together.
They were super-duper delicious!

00:09:16.681 --> 00:09:18.433 position:50% align:center
[ALL gasp]

00:09:18.516 --> 00:09:20.894 position:50% align:center
Right, sit down!
We need to talk!

00:09:20.977 --> 00:09:23.897 position:50% align:center
[KIMI] Would love to,
but Kimi's a little busy, so--

00:09:23.980 --> 00:09:26.191 position:50% align:center
[YUKI] Secretary Kimi Todo,
a second year,

00:09:26.274 --> 00:09:29.444 position:50% align:center
appears to enjoy
instigating conflict.

00:09:29.527 --> 00:09:32.364 position:50% align:center
Okay, what is this?
Somebody's idea of a joke?

00:09:32.447 --> 00:09:33.907 position:50% align:center
That sign is ludicrous!

00:09:33.990 --> 00:09:38.536 position:50% align:center
And this room's a perpetual
mess. Honestly, people!

00:09:38.620 --> 00:09:41.664 position:50% align:center
[YUKI] Secretary Naohito
Sakuragi, a first year,

00:09:41.748 --> 00:09:43.208 position:50% align:center
is more than a
little high-strung.

00:09:43.291 --> 00:09:44.542 position:50% align:center
Kuragi, think you can work

00:09:44.626 --> 00:09:47.671 position:50% align:center
without spreading your
papers all over the place?!

00:09:47.754 --> 00:09:50.590 position:50% align:center
[YUKI] And treasurer Machi
Kuragi, a first year,

00:09:50.674 --> 00:09:53.927 position:50% align:center
looks at the floor most of the
time and barely ever speaks.

00:09:54.010 --> 00:09:55.220 position:50% align:center
Good grief.

00:09:55.303 --> 00:09:56.846 position:50% align:center
Are those two actually out
doing their rounds?

00:09:56.930 --> 00:09:59.641 position:50% align:center
Or maybe just trying
to get away from here.

00:10:01.518 --> 00:10:03.687 position:50% align:center
The flowers are
blooming beautifully.

00:10:03.770 --> 00:10:05.730 position:50% align:center
Thank you. It hasn't been easy.

00:10:05.814 --> 00:10:06.898 position:50% align:center
We're short on members,

00:10:06.981 --> 00:10:08.817 position:50% align:center
but we're doing the
best that we can.

00:10:08.900 --> 00:10:11.528 position:50% align:center
[YUKI] Well, I can tell
you're working hard.

00:10:11.611 --> 00:10:13.697 position:50% align:center
I'll try to come back by
and help you out,

00:10:13.780 --> 00:10:15.281 position:50% align:center
once my rounds are done.

00:10:15.365 --> 00:10:17.534 position:50% align:center
Wow. You'd really do that?

00:10:17.617 --> 00:10:19.119 position:50% align:center
Sure.

00:10:19.202 --> 00:10:21.454 position:50% align:center
