[YUKI] I constantly compare
myself to other people.

00:19:14.612 --> 00:19:17.866 position:50% align:center
Sometimes it feels like the
inferiority will swallow me,

00:19:17.949 --> 00:19:20.618 position:50% align:center
until I disappear completely.

00:19:20.702 --> 00:19:23.997 position:50% align:center
Looking at him,
so cool and confident,

00:19:24.080 --> 00:19:25.415 position:50% align:center
a voice in my head whispers

00:19:25.498 --> 00:19:29.711 position:50% align:center
that maybe he would be
a better president.

00:19:29.794 --> 00:19:33.548 position:50% align:center
And it's so hard not
to just run away,

00:19:33.631 --> 00:19:37.177 position:50% align:center
when that voice follows
me everywhere I go.

00:19:39.262 --> 00:19:41.431 position:50% align:center
[YUKI]
You're right.

00:19:41.514 --> 00:19:46.895 position:50% align:center
I lost it before. I was
out of line. I'm sorry.

00:19:48.688 --> 00:19:53.693 position:50% align:center
[YUKI] The most difficult
person of all... is me.

00:19:53.777 --> 00:19:59.741 position:50% align:center
Turns out I do have a
villain to fight: Myself.

00:19:59.824 --> 00:20:02.911 position:50% align:center
The enemy I should
be focusing on...

00:20:02.994 --> 00:20:05.538 position:50% align:center
...is the one I carry inside.

00:20:07.374 --> 00:20:08.792 position:50% align:center
[MANABE]
Hey.

00:20:10.085 --> 00:20:15.006 position:50% align:center
Where should I stand so I can
see the same things you do?

00:20:15.090 --> 00:20:17.175 position:50% align:center
Perspective, right?

00:20:17.258 --> 00:20:18.510 position:50% align:center
It's not something
I'm great with,

00:20:18.593 --> 00:20:22.013 position:50% align:center
so I end up hurting people.

00:20:22.097 --> 00:20:24.974 position:50% align:center
You reminded me of someone.

00:20:25.058 --> 00:20:29.145 position:50% align:center
Things you said,
she would've, too.

00:20:29.229 --> 00:20:32.649 position:50% align:center
It caught me off guard,
and I guess, yeah,

00:20:32.732 --> 00:20:34.901 position:50% align:center
I got a little pissed.

00:20:36.027 --> 00:20:38.947 position:50% align:center
I'm jealous.

00:20:39.030 --> 00:20:43.827 position:50% align:center
You're lucky because...
you get people.

00:20:45.578 --> 00:20:49.749 position:50% align:center
I screwed up, too,
n' lost it. Again.

00:20:49.833 --> 00:20:53.586 position:50% align:center
You'd think I would've learned
by now, but I guess not.

00:20:53.670 --> 00:20:54.379 position:50% align:center
Sorry.

00:20:54.462 --> 00:20:56.047 position:50% align:center
[GARDEN STUDENT A screams]

00:20:56.131 --> 00:21:00.010 position:50% align:center
Oh, no! The seedlings!
What did you do to them?!

00:21:00.093 --> 00:21:02.012 position:50% align:center
Whoa. Where'd you come from?

00:21:02.095 --> 00:21:03.346 position:50% align:center
It's my fault, by the way.

00:21:03.430 --> 00:21:05.098 position:50% align:center
[GARDEN STUDENT A]
I figured that much out already!

00:21:05.181 --> 00:21:07.017 position:50% align:center
Obviously the president
didn't do it!

00:21:07.100 --> 00:21:08.560 position:50% align:center
Wow, that's harsh.

00:21:08.643 --> 00:21:09.811 position:50% align:center
Tell ya what,

00:21:09.894 --> 00:21:12.731 position:50% align:center
I'll make it up to you
by planting all of them.

00:21:12.814 --> 00:21:14.691 position:50% align:center
I'm not so sure.

00:21:14.774 --> 00:21:16.067 position:50% align:center
The whole point of
the student council

00:21:16.151 --> 00:21:17.944 position:50% align:center
is to help our
fellow classmates.

00:21:18.028 --> 00:21:19.571 position:50% align:center
Am I right?

00:21:20.613 --> 00:21:25.076 position:50% align:center
[YUKI] You caught me off guard,
too, with your sincerity.

00:21:26.036 --> 00:21:28.163 position:50% align:center
I'm jealous.

00:21:29.831 --> 00:21:32.667 position:50% align:center
[YUKI]
It made me want to cry.

00:21:32.751 --> 00:21:35.337 position:50% align:center
I hope you don't expect
any help with this.

00:21:35.420 --> 00:21:39.466 position:50% align:center
Oh, come on. You're totally
killin' my motivation.

00:21:40.592 --> 00:21:45.347 position:50% align:center
[YUKI] I held my tears in,
but it wasn't easy.

00:21:48.350 --> 00:21:51.269 position:50% align:center
I'm very sorry! I was wrong.

00:21:51.353 --> 00:21:54.856 position:50% align:center
I regret my actions and
won't do such a thing again.

00:21:54.939 --> 00:21:57.442 position:50% align:center
Sorry about what?
And who are you?

00:21:57.525 --> 00:21:58.526 position:50% align:center
Good talk. I'm out!

00:21:58.610 --> 00:22:01.321 position:50% align:center
Hey! Seriously,
who the heck are you?

00:22:01.404 --> 00:22:03.281 position:50% align:center
Uh, you don't recognize
the vice president

00:22:03.365 --> 00:22:06.034 position:50% align:center
of the student council,
Kyon-Kyon?

00:22:07.827 --> 00:22:11.039 position:50% align:center
[YUKI] There will be conflict,
but if we can talk through it

00:22:11.122 --> 00:22:13.708 position:50% align:center
and learn to understand
each other...

00:22:15.126 --> 00:22:16.670 position:50% align:center
[chuckles]

00:22:18.254 --> 00:22:21.716 position:50% align:center
[YUKI] ...I'm starting to
think that working with him...

00:22:21.800 --> 00:22:24.886 position:50% align:center
...might not be such
a bad thing after all.

00:23:57.020 --> 00:23:59.189 position:50% align:center
[HATSUHARU]
"I might as well die, then."